data.name: label14.Text
data.value:
So to choose the right answer for every multiplication you have to click in the drop down list and click one of the options.
If your answer is right, after you hit the submit button, you will get a check next to the right asnswer.
If your answer is false you will get an X next of your answer.
Now if you get a score smaller than 4 in a test , the theory of multiplication of the specific table will show up next to your answers!

data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
If you pass the Final Review Test with a mark greater than 17 out of 20 then the button of the test turns green so you know you have passed it!
Now if you dont pass the test , get a score smaller than 10 out of 20, the button of the test turns into red and a banner under the title comes up which tells you to revise your multiplication theory!

data.name: label8.Text
data.value:
When you pass a test with an 8 or higher score, the button of the passed test turns into green so you know you have passed this section.
When you pass a test with a 5-7 score , the button of the passed test turns into orange so you know you have to put a bit more effort to get a green pass. (Green passes help you make your way to the Final Review Test)
When you get a score smaller than 5 then the button of the test sesction you got this score turns into red. That means you didn't pass the test and you have to try again harder this time.
